    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Balto.</placeName>
                <date>Saty</date> night</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Sepbr. 10/64</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear old Friend—</p>
            <p>Your brief note (dated the <date>10th</date><lb/> &amp; I <hi rend="underline"
                    >presume</hi>, written yesterday?)<lb/> reached me this morning.<lb/> I also
                desire to explain one<lb/> simple statement to you.<lb/> Owing—of course, to the
                “proverbial<lb/> neglect &amp; stupidity—<persName>Mr Ls</persName><lb/> dispatcher”
                I have recd<lb/> 2 nos. of the “Occt. for <hi rend="underline"
                    ><date>July</date></hi> &amp;<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">none</hi> for <date>August</date>, <hi rend="underline"
                    >therefore</hi> I<lb/> would not “refer to it” as requested.<lb/> These nos came
                during my<lb/> absence &amp; only today taking them<lb/> out for
                    <date>Sabbath</date> reading, I<lb/> discovered the above fact. <hi
                    rend="underline">Over</hi></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The <date>Sepbr</date> no came safely.<lb/> My natural impetuosity<lb/> dictated the
                first epistle, &amp;<lb/> you replied—”in same”.<lb/> Well! We have known<lb/> each
                other too long to<lb/> be ever angry with each<lb/> other! &amp; I remain<lb/> as
                from childhood</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yrs Resptfy &amp; affecty.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Josephine</persName>.</p>
            <p>Aunts desire kind regards, &amp;<lb/> thanks for your friendly<lb/> remembrance.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
